text: Anna Kallistová (born 30 October 1982) is a Czech volleyball player. She played at the 2009 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, and 2011 Women's European Volleyball League. She played for PVK Olymp Praha. == References == Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Czech volleyball players
